27/04/2003
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- At its party congress Saturday (26 April), the Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) elected Barisa Colak as its new leader.
Colak, who serves as security minister in the BiH government, has been HDZ's acting chairman.
Following Saturday's vote, he pledged to work for the party unity and efficiency, acknowledging difficulties in enforcing leadership decisions.
(Onasa, BHTV1, HINA - 26/04/03)
